               <head>Zad al-musafirin</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Zād al-musāfirīn by Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_15661-item1" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083116 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158">
                     <author key="person_220924367" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="Persian_0074">Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="Persian_0074" type="supplied">محمد مهدی بن علی نقی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20103" change="#ids-cleanup">Zād al-musāfirīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20103" change="#ids-cleanup">زاد المسافرين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A guide to preservation of health and self-treatment for travellers, by Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī. The work was completed at Isfahan in 1141/1728, during the Afghan invasion, for <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f3058" role="pat">Mīrzā Muḥammad Ismā‘īl</persName>.</p>
                        <p>It comprises two parts (maṭlab): on preventive health and hygiene, and on the treatment of certain ailments treatable without the aid of a physician.</p>
                        <p>The present manuscript is slightly incomplete at the end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
